---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/main.astro";
import PageHeading from "../../components/ui/page-heading.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<MainLayout title="My DevOps Journey with OpenTelemetry">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto my-12 sm:my-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <PageHeading
        title='OpenTelemetry <span class="text-blue-500">Astronomy Shop</span>'
      />
      <p
        class="text-base md:text-xl leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto"
      >
        I've been working with the OpenTelemetry Astronomy Shop Demo to gain
        hands-on experience in DevOps. Itâ€™s helped me understand how real-world
        applications are structured, monitored, and managed.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4 mb-8">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-demo"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 rounded-md bg-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-700 text-white dark:text-gray-100 text-sm font-medium shadow-md hover:scale-105 hover:bg-gray-700 dark:hover:bg-gray-600 transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"
        >
          <Icon name="mdi:github" class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
          <span>See the Code</span>
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://opentelemetry.io/docs/demo/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 rounded-md bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 dark:bg-blue-700 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 text-white text-sm font-medium shadow-md hover:scale-105 transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"
        >
          <Icon name="mdi:book-open-variant" class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
          <span>Read the Docs</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Featured Image -->
    <div
      class="mb-12 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
    >
      <img
        src="/assets/images/projects/devops-ecom-1.png"
        alt="ColorSense Dashboard"
        class="w-full h-auto"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h2
        class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8 text-center text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
      >
        My Project Steps: A Simple Overview
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
        Here's a simplified look at how I set up the OpenTelemetry Astronomy
        Shop Demo to learn about DevOps:
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div
          class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-md transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 flex items-center"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:aws" class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" />
            Cloud Setup (AWS)
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
          >
            <li>Used Terraform to get things running on the cloud (AWS).</li>
            <li>Made sure all the parts could communicate with each other.</li>
            <li>Set up a web address for the application.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-md transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400 flex items-center"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:docker" class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" />
            Containers (Docker)
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
          >
            <li>Put each piece of the application into its own container.</li>
            <li>Managed these containers for the app.</li>
            <li>Tested the app on my computer using these containers.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-md transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 flex items-center"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:kubernetes" class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" />
            Running on a Cluster (Kubernetes)
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
          >
            <li>Used Kubernetes on AWS (EKS) to run the application.</li>
            <li>
              Set up how the different parts of the app are started and managed.
            </li>
            <li>Made sure the app could store its data.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-md transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 flex items-center"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:terraform" class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" />
            Setup as Code (Terraform)
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
          >
            <li>Wrote down the setup for AWS as code using Terraform.</li>
            <li>Made sure only one person could make changes at a time.</li>
            <li>Automated the process of setting up the AWS infrastructure.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-md transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 flex items-center"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:git" class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" />
            Keeping Things Synced (GitOps with Argo CD)
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
          >
            <li>
              Used Argo CD to manage how the app gets updated based on the code
              in Git.
            </li>
            <li>Automated the deployment of new versions of the app.</li>
            <li>Defined how the Kubernetes setup should be in code.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div
          class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-md transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-yellow-600 dark:text-yellow-400 flex items-center"
          >
            <Icon name="mdi:github" class="w-6 h-6 mr-2" />
            Automated Deployment
          </h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2"
          >
            <li>Automated building and testing of application code.</li>
            <li>Automated the deployment process.</li>
            <li>Automatically deployed code to Kubernetes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
        Key DevOps Concepts
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <Icon
            name="mdi:puzzle-outline"
            class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mt-0.5 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
          />
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
              >Microservices:</span
            >
            Managing many small services adds complexity but increases flexibility.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <Icon
            name="mdi:code-braces"
            class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-500 mt-0.5 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
          />
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
              >Infrastructure as Code:</span
            >
            Using code for setup ensures consistency and simplifies management.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <Icon
            name="mdi:anchor"
            class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-500 mt-0.5 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
          />
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
              >Container Orchestration:</span
            >
            Kubernetes makes it easier to run and scale applications efficiently.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <Icon
            name="mdi:rocket"
            class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-500 mt-0.5 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
          />
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
              >CI/CD Pipelines:</span
            >
            Automation speeds up deployments and reduces potential errors.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <Icon
            name="mdi:git"
            class="w-6 h-6 text-teal-500 mt-0.5 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
          />
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"
              >GitOps:</span
            >
            Managing everything through Git ensures reliability and clarity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
